# JARVIS Page Template

When creating or modifying pages in the app, use this standard layout so all pages look consistent.

## Header Template (use on all pages)

- **Left:** Frame (Navigation — JARVIS frame, 80×80). Same size for all headers.
- **Center:** Page title text, centered.
- **Right:** Icon for the **next hierarchical level** (parent section), same size as the left frame (80×80). Link wraps the icon; no "← Section" text link.

Do not use an arrow or text link (e.g. "← Cycling") for back navigation. Use the right-corner icon only.

## Required Structure

```tsx
"use client";

import Link from "next/link";
import Navigation from "../components/Navigation";  // or correct relative path
import CircuitBackground from "../hub/CircuitBackground";
import ParentSectionIcon from "../ParentSectionIcon";  // e.g. CyclingIcon for pages under /bike

const hubTheme = {
  primary: "#00D9FF",
  secondary: "#67C7EB",
  background: "#000000",
  cardBg: "rgba(0, 217, 255, 0.05)",
};

export default function PageName() {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen hud-scifi-bg relative" style={{ backgroundColor: hubTheme.background, color: hubTheme.primary }}>
      <CircuitBackground />
      <main className="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 max-w-4xl relative z-10">
        <div className="grid grid-cols-3 items-center gap-4 mb-8">
          <div className="flex justify-start w-20 h-20 min-w-20 min-h-20">
            <Navigation />
          </div>
          <h2 className="text-2xl font-semibold hud-text text-center">Page Title</h2>
          <div className="flex justify-end">
            <Link href="/parent" title="Parent Section" aria-label="Parent Section" className="inline-flex items-center justify-center transition-transform hover:scale-110" style={{ width: 80, height: 80, minWidth: 80, minHeight: 80 }}>
              <ParentSectionIcon className="shrink-0" style={{ width: 80, height: 80, minWidth: 80, minHeight: 80 }} stroke={hubTheme.primary} />
            </Link>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Page content — no "← Section" link below header */}
      </main>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Key Conventions

- **Background:** `min-h-screen hud-scifi-bg`, `backgroundColor: hubTheme.background`
- **Main:** `container mx-auto px-4 py-8 max-w-4xl relative z-10` (use `max-w-6xl` for wider content)
- **Header columns:** Left holds the frame (80×80px). Right column uses `flex justify-end` (no fixed width) so the icon sits all the way to the right; icon and link use explicit `style={{ width: 80, height: 80, minWidth: 80, minHeight: 80 }}` to match the frame size.
- **Title:** `text-2xl font-semibold hud-text text-center`
- **Cards:** `hud-card rounded-lg p-6 border border-[#00D9FF]/20`
- **Buttons:** `border border-[#00D9FF]/50 bg-[rgba(0,217,255,0.15)] text-[#00D9FF] hover:bg-[rgba(0,217,255,0.25)]`
- **Secondary text:** `style={{ color: hubTheme.secondary }}` or `text-[#67C7EB]`

## Child Pages (e.g. under Foods & Ingredients)

- Use the header template with the parent-section icon in the right corner (same size as left frame).
- For nutrition child pages, use `NutritionBackIcon` in the right column if that pattern exists; otherwise use the section icon that links to the parent.
